{"TopicId":201495,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Peridoot\u0026#039;s smol plane challange!","CreatedByName":"peridoot","CreatedById":211038,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-07T00:16:27Z","PageNum":2,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"dnbattley","CreatedById":176526,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-15T03:40:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI won\u0027t submit anything technically legal, but physics-defying,\u00A0but suffice to say 3-part or \u0026lt;500kg manned flight can be achieved... \u0026gt;:D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will, however post a link to a micro \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E I made some time back, rated for 3 minutes of relatively fun flying...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Dcii2LD.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Dcii2LD.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XLfZlIw.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XLfZlIw.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-15T07:44:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223954574\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618444937\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211038\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022peridoot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, peridoot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis plane meets every requirement except for the flight time. but because this was made before that was specified, i will allow it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes that mean powered flight time or time aloft?\u00A0 Because it will certainly glide for longer than 30 seconds.\u00A0 I just hit the chute immediately.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152460-swjr-swis/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022152460\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152460-swjr-swis/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@swjr-swis\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u0022Reckless Machines of Death\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat sounds pretty par\u00A0for the course in many Kerbal challenges\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022\u0026amp;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_cool.png\u0022 title=\u0022\u0026amp;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-04-15T18:52:43Z\u0022 title=\u002204/15/2021 06:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EApril 15, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Klapaucius\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"peridoot","CreatedById":211038,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-15T23:00:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223952554\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618110598\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/10/2021 at 10:09 PM, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA small kerballed supersonic plane on a single Juno and with an actual cockpit:\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/swjr-swis/LT-Supersonic-II\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/swjr-swis/LT-Supersonic-II\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1.68t wet weight, 4400 funds, only 68 science points to spend on the tech tree.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlies 1 kerbal at mach 1.6 @ 11 km using 0.02 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Liquid Fuel\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Liquid Fuel\u0022\u003ELF\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E/s, cruise range upwards of 800km.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/LIgYx1d.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022LIgYx1d.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/LIgYx1d.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLands horizontally, chute for braking (the smallest low tech gear have no brakes of their own).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/vOGrC7X.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022vOGrC7X.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/vOGrC7X.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it count?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nehhhh with the large pod i will have to say this wont count because a lot of designs im looking for could almost FIT inside a pod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-15T23:31:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223955160\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618527600\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211038\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022peridoot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, peridoot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nehhhh with the large pod i will have to say this wont count because a lot of designs im looking for could almost FIT inside a pod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFair enough. That one fulfilled its purpose already in a different challenge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBtw, aren\u0027t you adding \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/201495-peridoots-smol-plane-challange/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=3954594\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ethe other entries you approved\u003C/a\u003E to the leaderboards?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Max von Kerman","CreatedById":211147,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T00:05:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDangit i cat even fly a space shuttle so plz dont make me fly a\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:9px;\u0022\u003ETINY\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0plane \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T01:00:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223955184\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618531527\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211147\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Max von Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n55 minutes ago, Max von Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDangit i cat even fly a space shuttle so plz dont make me fly a\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:9px;\u0022\u003ETINY\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0plane \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026lt;affecting my best Jeremy Clarkson impression\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome say the space shuttle was a mistake. Some say it\u0027s little more than a flying brick and shouldn\u0027t have been flown in the first place.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll we know is, it stalls on stick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-04-16T01:00:55Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2021 01:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by swjr-swis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Max von Kerman","CreatedById":211147,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T01:08:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223955210\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618534803\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026lt;affecting my best Jeremy Clarkson impression\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome say the space shuttle was a mistake. Some say it\u0027s little more than a flying brick and shouldn\u0027t have been flown in the first place.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll we know is, it stalls on stick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe thig is that i don\u0027t know how to fly anything plane related, I\u0027m more of a rocket guy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*Everytime i try landing a shuttle, it does a colombia style spin and break up.*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T07:23:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI managed 50 seconds of air time and even landed it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is the craft file:\u00A0\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Klapaucius/Poe-Sepratron-Microlite\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Klapaucius/Poe-Sepratron-Microlite\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for this very fun challenge. You inspired me to create my own!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/K0Iw9qx-kbU?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-04-16T07:33:45Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2021 07:33  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Klapaucius\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"peridoot","CreatedById":211038,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T13:59:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni am getting to the leader board part. its just really hard to decide!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DRAG0Nmon","CreatedById":196609,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T18:02:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs the plane allowed to take slight damage upon landing?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vyznev","CreatedById":90620,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T18:04:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223950190\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617754587\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211038\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022peridoot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/7/2021 at 3:16 AM, peridoot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe challange is simple: make the smallest aircraft possible in stock KSP (you can use DLCs)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRULES:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmust have some form of part that can generate lift (like a evelon)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes a Kerbal with a parachute count as a lift-generating part? If yes, let me present\u2026 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022FwRkQLf.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002260.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/FwRkQLf.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCritics have called the BYOA rocket paraglider \u0022nothing more than a sepratron strapped to a steel chair\u0022, but while this may have been an accurate description of the early development versions, the new advanced electric attitude control system \u2014 installed after test flights revealed that Kerbals could not properly steer using their parachute while sitting in a chair* \u2014 makes the BYOA much more than that. Yet it\u0027s still just as fun to ride!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022caQDBSQ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002260.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/caQDBSQ.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:11px;\u0022\u003E*) Attempts to develop an even more lightweight version that would omit both the electric guidance system and the chair, and simply attach the rocket directly to the pilot\u0027s butt, have so far been unsuccessful.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe latest production version also adds a high impact tolerance grip pad for extra landing safety. (If you don\u0027t have the Breaking Ground DLC installed, don\u0027t worry \u2014 the craft is fully stock except for the grip pad and flies just fine without it, it\u0027s just a lot harder to land intact while staying under the 7 m/s impact tolerance of the cuboctagonal strut.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022x5A8alw.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002260.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/x5A8alw.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOperating instructions: Before launch, turn \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E on and preferably switch to fine control mode and open the pilot\u0027s right-click menu. Stage to launch. Pitch up during launch for a longer flight. Deploy chute near apogee and pitch down to about 5\u00B0 below the horizon. If stalled, temporarily pitch down more until you gain enough forward speed, then pull up again. The optimal pitch and ground speed for gliding and landing seem to be a few degrees below horizontal and about 12 m/s. When steering, make sure to keep the center of the navball below the horizon or you\u0027ll quickly lose speed and stall. When landing, pitch up a little just before touchdown to kill excess horizontal velocity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022A56lEt2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002260.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/A56lEt2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ztWMlcL.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002260.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/ztWMlcL.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbalX link: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/vyznev/BYOA-Rocket-Paraglider\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/vyznev/BYOA-Rocket-Paraglider\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"peridoot","CreatedById":211038,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T19:08:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223954669\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618458029\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176526\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dnbattley\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/14/2021 at 10:40 PM, dnbattley said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI won\u0027t submit anything technically legal, but physics-defying,\u00A0but suffice to say 3-part or \u0026lt;500kg manned flight can be achieved... \u0026gt;:D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will, however post a link to a micro \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E I made some time back, rated for 3 minutes of relatively fun flying...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Dcii2LD.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Dcii2LD.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Dcii2LD.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XLfZlIw.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XLfZlIw.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XLfZlIw.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni kinda want to see this 3 part plane.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DRAG0Nmon","CreatedById":196609,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T19:29:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll you kids with your new-fangled \u0022SRBs\u0022 and your fancy \u0022jet engines \u0022, back in my day we had to use propellers if we wanted to fly!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/sw_Ac-iZbdc?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5,370 funds,\u00A0 799kg with Pables Kerman on board and 705kg without her.\u00A0 6.804 cubic meters (dimensions are shown in the video) and made with 22 of the finest parts. Its rather large compared to the other planes here, but its also powered by eight pieces of metal spinning at 460 RPM. I\u0027m also positive that I\u00A0can make it smaller,\u00A0 so now i have something to do over the weekend.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"peridoot","CreatedById":211038,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T19:32:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223955714\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618601346\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196609\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DRAG0Nmon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, DRAG0Nmon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll you kids with your new-fangled \u0022SRBs\u0022 and your fancy \u0022jet engines \u0022, back in my day we had to use propellers if we wanted to fly!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/sw_Ac-iZbdc?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5,370 funds,\u00A0 799kg with Pables Kerman on board and 705kg without her.\u00A0 6.804 cubic meters (dimensions are shown in the video) and made with 22 of the finest parts. Its rather large compared to the other planes here, but its also powered by eight pieces of metal spinning at 460 RPM. I\u0027m also positive that I\u00A0can make it smaller,\u00A0 so now i have something to do over the weekend.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsooooo uh that i that part that the chair sits on? i see you have mods. i did not say mods are allowed. i said DLCs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DRAG0Nmon","CreatedById":196609,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T19:35:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/211038-peridoot/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022211038\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/211038-peridoot/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@peridoot\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I have \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E, Scatterer, and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E installed for visuals and information. The chair is sitting on 3 rotated and offset stock fuel cells, which provide 4.5 electric charge for the propellers, which consume 3.2 electric charge. The craft is entirely stock, as said in the vid\u0027s description.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"peridoot","CreatedById":211038,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-16T19:37:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nah. ok well you got a valid plane! have a badge!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dnbattley","CreatedById":176526,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-17T07:14:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223955703\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618600122\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211038\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022peridoot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, peridoot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni kinda want to see this 3 part plane.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere you go \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u00A0 Raw video footage of me taking it for a spin to the island and back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/tKDIzRC8-Oo?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dnbattley","CreatedById":176526,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-17T07:34:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd, while I\u0027m at it, a flyable\u00A0lightweight version. 251kg, without pilot. Flag is not used as a lifting surface, so I believe this is still within the rules.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022h3KpZTK.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/h3KpZTK.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlys quite nicely\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022TCUBOsK.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/TCUBOsK.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThough landing is a little bit\u00A0hairy - and no reaction wheel to assist...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022erVJ4sg.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/erVJ4sg.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"peridoot","CreatedById":211038,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-17T15:33:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223956045\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618644859\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176526\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dnbattley\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, dnbattley said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd, while I\u0027m at it, a flyable\u00A0lightweight version. 251kg, without pilot. Flag is not used as a lifting surface, so I believe this is still within the rules.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/h3KpZTK.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022h3KpZTK.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/h3KpZTK.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlys quite nicely\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/TCUBOsK.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022TCUBOsK.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/TCUBOsK.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThough landing is a little bit\u00A0hairy - and no reaction wheel to assist...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/erVJ4sg.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022erVJ4sg.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/erVJ4sg.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni did say no kraken drives. so this wont be allowed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"peridoot","CreatedById":211038,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-17T18:04:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223955661\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618596127\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196609\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DRAG0Nmon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/16/2021 at 1:02 PM, DRAG0Nmon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs the plane allowed to take slight damage upon landing?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni would say if more than 25% is destoryed you have to do a redo\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dnbattley","CreatedById":176526,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-18T01:32:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223956214\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618673625\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211038\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022peridoot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, peridoot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did say no kraken drives. so this wont be allowed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s fair: I didn\u0027t see it in the original rules, but you did subsequently comment that way. I think I can do a three part unmanned version which doesn\u0027t use a Kraken engine, but does equally exploit Ksp\u0027s engine...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vyznev","CreatedById":90620,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-18T06:22:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223956483\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618709558\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176526\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dnbattley\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, dnbattley said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think I can do a three part unmanned version which doesn\u0027t use a Kraken engine, but does equally exploit Ksp\u0027s engine...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTechnically, the original version of my BYOA had only three parts \u2014 a command chair, a sepratron and a cubic strut (to serve as the root part for attaching the other two) \u2014 and used no exploits. But it was basically uncontrollable after chute deployment, so the only way to land it without breaking any of the three parts was by pure luck.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I did realize that I could trim the six-part version I posted earlier down to just five parts, since the reaction wheel can serve as the root part, making the strut superfluous. And technically I could even get rid of the grip pad too, if I\u0027m allowed to break one of the four remaining parts on landing as the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E mentioned above. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E Or I just need to learn how to land more gently \u2014 hitting the ground at less than 8 m/s to avoid any parts breaking is definitely possible, just hard.) \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dnbattley","CreatedById":176526,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-18T11:18:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, so two more craft to throw into the mix:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. 4 part, exploit-(but not kraken-) powered, so infinite range (as long as the battery holds out, anyway). It was more stable\u00A0when I moved the aileron to the back, but flew in either configuration:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022wOvlcvL.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/wOvlcvL.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. A actually legitimate entry, although I still haven\u0027t managed to land it successfully (it\u0027s highly unstable): 3 parts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XO2jQvS.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XO2jQvS.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-18T12:39:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit edit: Okay, this is my final submission. 1841 Funds, 78 kg, 4 parts, 0.4 * 0.4 * 0.6 = 0.144 m\u003Csup\u003E3\u003C/sup\u003E.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s basically the same as the previous entry, minus the solar panel. It turns out it has juice for over 30 seconds in the air with the 5 EC carried by that little probe core. I don\u0027t think this design can be shrunk much further, and it\u0027s clearly the minimum part count for a copter design in any case, since you need lift \u002B power \u002B control and you can\u0027t subtract any of the parts without losing one of the three.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/sqFDPl1Pjyc?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1766 Funds, 5 parts, 83 kg, 0.5 x 0.6 x 1.2m = 0.36 m\u003Csup\u003E3\u003C/sup\u003E,\u00A0no exploits, no clipping, unlimited daytime endurance.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt can only go up or down, but the ability to\u00A0 go sideways wasn\u0027t specified...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/b4EXHXr4rN0?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCraft file:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Brikoleur/mc\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Brikoleur/mc\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: An even tinier variant, \u00A0although a bit more expensive; with clipping since that\u0027s allowed. 1916 Funds, 5 parts, 83 kg, 0.4*0.6*0.6m = 0.144 m\u003Csup\u003E3\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022pPr42Pw.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022120.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/pPr42Pw.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/hYpLtDsn7PA?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-04-18T15:30:04Z\u0022 title=\u002204/18/2021 03:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EApril 18, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Guest\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vyznev","CreatedById":90620,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-18T13:29:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223956636\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221618749544\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167629\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Brikoleur\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n38 minutes ago, Brikoleur said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt can only go up or down, but the ability to\u00A0 go sideways wasn\u0027t specified...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStick a reaction wheel on there and it\u0027ll go sideways too just fine. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022FeJgWd5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.67\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/FeJgWd5.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003E(Well, OK, not exactly fine. It\u0027s kinda janky to control because the reaction wheel keeps \u0022slipping\u0022 and letting the craft rotate by a few degrees every few seconds so you have to keep correcting the attitude. That might be a bug, but KSP reaction wheels work by pure magic anyway so who knows. But it flies and is basically controllable enough to land anywhere you want.)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}